content:
First off I would like to mention, I have watched the entire series and have come back to finish and give a complete review of Guilty Crown. Although this Anime series has many faults, I wouldn't say that it's complete garbage like so many people are making it out to be. I actually found Guilty Crown to be a beautiful piece of work despite it's faults. ♥
Story :: The plot of Guilty Crown is a weaker element of the series. In the beginning it starts of strong, but the further it goes the more it lingers and becomes hazy. However, I did really love thestory, I think the issue comes with how it's presented and exicuted. A lot of details are left out and never explained all that well leaving many plot wholes and inconsistencies.  I wish that Guilty Crown went more in depth in the story so we could get a better understanding. Many viewers will point out similarities with other series. Guilty Crown contains many cliche and inspirations from other series. But to be honest, this never bothered me much. Although I did notice similar ideas, I found more differences. Overall I enjoyed the story, but I think it could of used many improvements! It was pretty good, but not great.  I give plot a score of 6 {Fair} 


Art :: This a very strong point in the series. The animation and artwork is stunning! I could tell that the creators put a lot of thought into character designs and overall artwork. The animation is smooth and the color is vivid, giving it great detail. The battle scenes ate done beautifully and the quality never strays. I love the art style! Probably one the best animation I've seen in Anime. (: For Art, I give Guilty Crown a score of 8 {Very Good} 


Sound :: The music and sound is another strong point along with the animation. The songs from the opening & ending themes warmed my heart. The lyrics are beautiful & the music is captivating. Inori's songs give Guilty Crown a nice touch. The background music is also nice. Many fit nicely and create the mood. Overall, Guilty Crown has a great soundtrack! I give it a score of 9 {Great!} 


Characters :: Although the series presents many interesting characters with a variety of personalities, this is were things get sloppy. I felt that the characters never fully developed throughout the series. There are some moments of change, but it becomes inconsistent. I felt like I couldn't fully feel or connect with many of the characters, not to say that I felt nothing. Something about Inori's unconditional love for Shu, Shu being able to see Inori as true person instead of just an empty shell, and Gai's weaknesses under his facade & strong desire to be with Mana. It moved me and touched my heart. Guilty Crown shows glimpses of  the deep desires and depth within the characters, which gives off an interesting vibe & energy. I found the connection between the main characters to spark my imagination. Many will say that they have no true meaningful connection, but I feel that they do, even when it's not expressed through words. Although I liked many of the characters, the development needed some work. A few characters where rememberable, while others are easily forgotten.  I give characters a score of 6 {Fair} 


Enjoyment :: All in All, I really enjoyed this Anime! I found it captivating and a nice series overall. However, it did suffer from minor cliche elements,  plot holes, inconsiticies, and lack of total character development. But that doesn't automatically make me hate it. I found beauty in the story & characters despite there faults, nothings perfect! It gave me inspiration and sparked my imagination. I give Guilty Crown a rating of 8 {Very Good} 


My overall score for the series is a 7 {Good} 


♥ Emily
